â€”

In the highlands of Anahuac, where the sun walked daily across the sacred sky and the people chanted to many gods, a child was born into royaltyâ€”but destined for exile. His name was Nezahualcoyotl, the fasting coyote, prince of Texcoco, poet of truth, and prophet of the unseen God.

