â€œDo we truly live on Earth? Not forever on Earth; only a little while here. Let us do good, for we are all travelers.â€

He called for justice, wisdom, and restraint. He reminded rulers that no crown outlives the dust. He urged the people to seek what is real, not what is loud.

â€œThe Giver of Life hides himself. Yet He lives in each breath, and in the sorrow of the heart, He listens.â€

â€”

