In the cities of America, where towers of pride rose and men chased shadows, he built shrines of peace. He founded the Selfâ€‘Realization Fellowship, and from its altar streamed teachings that blended scripture with science, prayer with practice, east with west.

Many called him prophet, others called him saintâ€”but he called himself a humble messenger. He declared:

